I have a simple node.js script:

``` javascript
var tree = require("process-tree");

var text = "text";

tree(5369, function (err, children) {
    console.log(JSON.stringify(children));
})
```

My package.json:

``` json
{
    "name": "name",
    "description": "description",
    "author": "author",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "main": "pathToMain",
    "dependencies": {
        "process-tree": "*"
    }
}
```

I set a breakpoint into the for loop and try to find the variable `text`. It is nowhere.

![editors](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/900690/19798650/a59f3748-9cf2-11e6-840e-91f478181b3c.gif)

I have code like this:

``` javascript
var text = "some text";

setTimeout(function () {
    console.log(text);
}, 0);
```

I have a breakpoint in the line of the `console.log` statement and when I delete the leading whitespace, the breakpoint is gone for me.

